    public interface SQLExpression<T>
extends SQLValue<T>
    An object that can produce a SQL expression suitable for use in a select statement. Though functionally the same as SQLValue when objects implement this interface the SQL fragment and the returned object should be equivalent allowing SQLExpressions to be combined together in java or in SQL without changing the meaning of the expression. SQLExpressions have to only generate a single result field so the add method must return 1;
